I still think nuclear power is safer. If an accident were to actually happen during the early ascent then it would be more disastrous but launching from an island would negate that. Reactors today are very reliable. How many nuclear naval vessels have either blewn up or lost control in past decades? A nuclear launcher would mean higher temperatures than regular reactors but the reduced fuel mass and lack of an oxydiser make the potential for an explosion far less than for chemical bosters. With 5 times the payload capacity you can build a far more robust vehicle with better safety features(and tiles). Looking over past deaths and near fatal catastrophes you can see that the two main causes have always been the combustible agents and a lack of energy. These risks are greatly reduced by nuclear engines. On top of that we would need 5 times less launches to achieve the same payload in space. <br>
